title.@value: Fetus or newborn affected by delivery by vacuum extractor

definition.@value: A condition characterised by findings in the fetus or newborn due to assisted birth in which intervention assistance is provided with a soft or hard plastic or metal cup attached by a tube to a suction device that fits firmly onto the head and attaches with suction (vacuum extractor, ventouse).

label.@value: Fetus and newborn affected by delivery by ventouse
